{
  "stem": "1857.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The truck never arrived, because then we found out that the truck was requisitioned by the Polish Army coming on their way to Krakow.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So-- and it-- luckily so, because if we would have wound up in Warsaw, we would have wound up in Warsaw Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And very few peopled survived that-- that ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My father-- men started leaving as the German Army was getting closer.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he left my mother, and my sister, and myself, and he left for the east.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the men marched east all the way practically to the Russian border.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And my father spent some time in city of Lvov, which was an eastern Polish city, under the Russian occupation there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He-- we were alone, and we had no means to-- to live on, because all the savings accounts in the bank were-- were closed by the Germans, so we couldn't touch our money.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the money wasn't worth that much either.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So my mother was selling some of her jewelry in order to sustain us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hm?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was 18.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so when the Germans walked in, the first months, nothing was happening.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then in October already, there was a van that was owned by a German cheese company.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we called the van Kaesewagen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When the van showed itself up in the Jewish section of Krakow, we knew that they're catching Jews for hard labor.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And sure enough, as soon as the van drove into the Jewish section, few German soldiers ran out of it and were catching people on the street who were close to the van, and putting them in the van, taking them for hard labor.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Some came back.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some didn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This I remember-- that-- that van I remember vividly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It even had a picture a-- of cheese on it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
